content:
Good evening,

I have had issues with submitting pset4, but I was able to do the checkoff. I used my two late days + 1 day from S^3 to turn it in. I think that maybe the website was accepting any late answers. When I look at the notes for the autograder, I get a

ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'hamcrest'

error. This happened on all test cases, resulting in an autograder score of 0.

I don't understand, can you please look into this? Thank you for your help.
subject: Pset4 Website Difficulty

content: Did you import a module called "hamcrest" in your code?
Yeah, I don't know why that is in my code. I think that might have been the result of autocompletion. Should I reupload the file to the website without the line that calls for the problematic module?
I just resubmitted to the website without that line, and I am no longer receiving the "failed all test cases" message from earlier. I am sorry for the inconvenience.
